HEADWORD: Interchain
<hw>In`ter*chain"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Interchained</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Interchaining</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To link
together; to unite closely or firmly, as by a chain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Two bosoms <qex>interchained</qex> with an oath.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interchange</ent>⟦br⟧
